  "target_response": {
    "text": "No — that's a healthy pace, not a dangerous one. At your 81 kg, losing 0.5 kg a week is roughly 0.6% of bodyweight per week, comfortably inside the commonly recommended ceiling of about 1% per week. And the fact that it came from one small, sustainable change — cutting snacks — is the best version of weight loss there is. The genuine warning signs would look different: loss accelerating on its own, energy or training quality falling away, disrupted periods, or finding yourself skipping meals. None of that is in your picture — your recovery has held at 73% and your sleep and resting heart rate are steady at their usual levels. So keep doing exactly what you're doing, and expect the rate to slow naturally as your weight comes down. That slowdown is normal physiology, not failure.",
